<div id="review_2895277236" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2895277236" />
    <a title="Maria Espadinha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20749430-maria-espadinha"><img alt="Maria Espadinha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1595262289p2/20749430.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2895277236?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria Espadinha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria Espadinha" href="/user/show/20749430-maria-espadinha">Maria Espadinha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51102530-the-real-happiness">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2895277236" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17026234267205356061">Philosophical Laughs <br/><br/><br/>The author dedicates this book to a girl who is half of his life, gave him life and taught him a lot (everything?!) about love! Moreover, she also happens to be the muse of his writing...<br/><br/>Being myself a girl (a senior one, but still 😜...), the moment I absorbed these words, my interest was trapped and my expectations became mountain climbers!...<br/><br/>A book about happiness, inspired by a girl capable of inflicting (not the fitting word, but I thoroughly like it😜) so much love and l</span>
  <span id="freeText17026234267205356061" style="display:none">Philosophical Laughs <br /><br /><br />The author dedicates this book to a girl who is half of his life, gave him life and taught him a lot (everything?!) about love! Moreover, she also happens to be the muse of his writing...<br /><br />Being myself a girl (a senior one, but still 😜...), the moment I absorbed these words, my interest was trapped and my expectations became mountain climbers!...<br /><br />A book about happiness, inspired by a girl capable of inflicting (not the fitting word, but I thoroughly like it😜) so much love and life to another being of her own kind, should be, as a corollary of some simple premises, a reliable source of happiness to its readers. However, while having these rambling thoughts, I was still in the Dedication Page, which meant I could have been... eventually... utterly wrong, but... fortunately for me and the author (who’ll be entitled to a 4 glowing stars review), I was spot on!...<br /><br />In a Nutshell, this is a humorous book about Real Happiness in a journey of faith, love and some stupidity, which means the title says it all 😉😊<br />Read it if you’re in the mood for a good bunch of philosophical laughs 🤩🤩🤪<br /><br />I know I should be gone by now, but I can’t do it before showing off the famous Dedication Page that thoroughly hooked my heart:<br /><br />Dedicated To... <br /><br />A girl... Who gave me life <br />A girl… Who is half of my life <br />A girl… Who taught me “what is love” in life <br />A girl… Whom I gave life <br />A girl… Who gave life to this novel <br /><br />And finally… <br />A man… Who spent his entire life just to make my life better…<br /><br />Now, tell me... didn’t this hook your heart , too?!... 😊😉</span>
  <a data-text-id="17026234267205356061" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


