  <span id="freeText8695810473176396161" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1607825800i/30517157._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This is an amazing read. The whole story is depicted intelligently.The story gives us the insight view of today's society, the problems which ruined our society these days, and their possible solution to overcome these problems with beautiful and worthy tips and advices.A few of them are quoted below which I like the most. <br><br>This is how happiness is defined in this book: <br><br><blockquote>“I guess any happiness that keeps you happy and relax and calm by heart is real happiness.Any act that makes your heart happy and gives joy to it is the lasting one. No hard feelings, no regrets, no what ifs.Just peace. When people get real happiness they laugh while being chained.They laugh at the prison cells.The laugh while being tortured. Because this inner satisfaction is more than anything in the world and they know the importance of it more than any one.” </blockquote><br><br>At one place, the writer described purity, friendship and relationship as:<br><br><blockquote>“Purity means true love. Friendship means always available.This relationship means the only person you will call on a rainy day.” </blockquote><br><br>Perfect healer: <br><br><b>“Time is not a healer, God is, let the God make the scenarios.” </b><br><br>A worderful read for those who are in search of true faith. I will highly recommend it to all those who wants to know the truth and makes their life truely amazing.</span>
