<div id="review_2888109307" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2888109307" />
    <a title="Habib Rahman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/99578413-habib-rahman"><img alt="Habib Rahman" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2888109307?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Habib Rahman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Habib Rahman" href="/user/show/99578413-habib-rahman">Habib Rahman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2888109307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15280715330334445160">The Real Happiness: &quot;Now he knew, he observed that human body is continuously deteriorating. If we don’t die then one day we will be mourning and shouting like this deer and no one will be able to solve our pain, no medics no love, nothing will be curable enough.&quot;<br/><br/>This book is entitled with the most appropriate title, today when everything is so broadly virtual, someone stands to talk about the real, highly possible and most peer aspect of our existence. Starting from the benchmark of faith, towa</span>
  <span id="freeText15280715330334445160" style="display:none">The Real Happiness: "Now he knew, he observed that human body is continuously deteriorating. If we don’t die then one day we will be mourning and shouting like this deer and no one will be able to solve our pain, no medics no love, nothing will be curable enough."<br /><br />This book is entitled with the most appropriate title, today when everything is so broadly virtual, someone stands to talk about the real, highly possible and most peer aspect of our existence. Starting from the benchmark of faith, towards essential support systems generally called friends or family and finally ceasing upon love; the manuscript is phenomenal. Written in a very simple and humble manner, the reader finds himself being curiously attracted towards this piece of art. <br /><br />The most pleasing part of the book is that it shows one how holding on to one vital loop can engage you with the good and detach you from the un-necessary. It shows how one can stand to face what is eternally important and real in our lives and simultaneously how to deal with things that are unpleasantly available for us. <br />The book to me, is a small bag full of miniatures mysteries I would like to unravel and explore with smiles. It actually turned out to be a story of some stupidity and loads of faith upon the invincible.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15280715330334445160" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


