<div id="review_3016673355" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3016673355" />
    <a title="Sarah Ali" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100274114-sarah-ali"><img alt="Sarah Ali" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1580256156p2/100274114.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3016673355?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah Ali" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah Ali" href="/user/show/100274114-sarah-ali">Sarah Ali</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51102530-the-real-happiness">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3016673355" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10325939783632544310">in this world where faith is a myth, land God is lost, a person with entirely different assumptions was forced to into a mismanaged crowd to live for four years.<br/><br/>Within the bunch of beings, he found people with almost similar journey. Faith was his journey and every journey has companions, like passion, believes, doubts, regrets, demons and god. But this time he found some other mates too.<br/><br/>A lost faith in relationships (other mate)<br/>A lost faith in God (hazel)<br/>A lost faith in society (philosopher)<br/>A l</span>
  <span id="freeText10325939783632544310" style="display:none">in this world where faith is a myth, land God is lost, a person with entirely different assumptions was forced to into a mismanaged crowd to live for four years.<br /><br />Within the bunch of beings, he found people with almost similar journey. Faith was his journey and every journey has companions, like passion, believes, doubts, regrets, demons and god. But this time he found some other mates too.<br /><br />A lost faith in relationships (other mate)<br />A lost faith in God (hazel)<br />A lost faith in society (philosopher)<br />A lost faith in self (curly)<br /><br />Like every companion there were various reasons to be on the journey. But their destination was the same. So they explored some of the biggest myths of the world, like love, fate, choice and faith.<br /><br />This book is the story of very ordinary people of the society, with very extraordinary questions to explore. To understand this book, all you have to do is close your eyes and look closely.<br /><br />Targeted Age Group:: 14-40<br /><br />What Inspired You to Write Your Book?<br />I read alot of novels, and i felt that the pure love and romance is now almost gone. It is replaced with just sex, nudity and vulgarity. These can be the attraction factors but they are kind of easy attraction. The true art is to attract the readers without them to your novels by they way you write, by the characters you create. I just want to do that.<br /><br /><br />How Did You Come up With Your Characters?<br />Being the managing Director of my firm i meet a lot of people (willingly or unwillingly) every day. A part of some of them helped me create my characters. 🙂<br /><br />Book Sample<br />I started writing my diary when I reached my home, I mean my room.<br /><br />Simplicity is the best.<br />Simplest idea has the deepest roots in mind.<br />Simplest personality is the most adorable.<br />Simplest solution is appealing.<br />Simplest painting is eye catching.<br />Simplest poem is the most remembered.<br />Simplest novel is the best seller.<br />So.<br />I was not just fascinated by the idea of having most beautiful person with me.<br />Or.<br />Long hairs.<br />Beautiful eyes.<br />Smiles like shining stars.<br />Skin like silk.<br />They all, most of the time, come with serious complexities only a person facing them can understand.<br />I am simple.<br />And I simply love the idea.<br />That a person.<br />She.<br />Simply loves me.<br />That’s the best thing about her.<br />Brown hair, long by the way, very very long frankly.<br />Big eyes, very big indeed and too beautiful I must say.<br />Soft personality, so fragile and tender.<br />They all are side lines.<br />She loves me. That’s the simplest and most beautiful thought of her I have<br />She loves me.<br />I’ve seen that in her eyes, heard it in her voice, observed it in her goose bumps and adored it in her smiles. When she holds my hand, every inch of her soul shouts to me that she loves me.<br />I love you.<br /><br />My pen stopped like it’s the final sentence of my life, like it’s the best line I have ever written.<br />So no need to write any more, at least not on this topic.<br />So I switched off the lamp.<br />Closed the diary.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10325939783632544310" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


